cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with the problem of embedding graph metrics into other graph metrics with low structural complexity, which is a problem in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of shortest paths and structural relations, which are topics in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
